#: TheoryHarmony.cpp:207
msgid ""
"Music in minor keys has a different sound and emotional feel than music that "
"is in a major key. Music in a major key sounds bright and cheerful while "
"music that is in a minor key is sometimes described as sounding more solemn, "
"sad, mysterious, or ominous."
msgstr ""
"La música escrita en tonalidades menores crea sensaciones y sentimientos muy "
"distintos de la escrita en tonalidades mayores. En tonalidad mayor, la "
"música suena brillante y alegre, mientras que la música en tonalidad menor "
"se describe, muchas veces, como triste, solemne, misteriosa o inquietante."

#: TheoryHarmony.cpp:252
msgid ""
"Music in minor keys is usually described as sad, mysterious, solemn, or "
"ominous. When using the minor natural scale the music has also and ancient "
"sound, like medieval music. By raising the seventh degree a semitone, in "
"both minor harmonic and minor melodic scales, musicians found that the "
"created harmonies make the music feel more strongly centered on the tonic "
"(you will learn about this in more advanced lessons) avoiding this "
"'medieval' feeling."
msgstr ""
"La música escrita en tonalidades menores se describe con frecuencia  como "
"triste, misteriosa, solemne o inquietante. La escala menor natural tiene "
"también una sonoridad 'antigua' como de música medieval. Al incrementar "
"medio tono  el séptimo grado, en las escalas menores armónicas y melódicas, "
"los músicos descubrieron que se evitaba la sonoridad 'medieval' y se creaban "
"armonías que transmitían mejor la sensación de tener un centro tonal "
